    "content": "CONSENSUS: APPROVED\n\nSteve Schoger here. The design proposal aligns with my visual guidance from earlier. A few confirmations:\n\n1. **Item row layout** matches what I recommended: `[Title] [date] [Activate] [Edit] [Delete]` -- simplest list item in the app with just two-level hierarchy (title + date).\n2. **Add form** is single-field (title only), matching the Projects add form pattern. Good.\n3. **BEM naming** follows the convention: `.someday-maybe`, `.someday-maybe-item`, `.someday-maybe-item__title`, etc.\n4. **\"Activate\" button** as the primary action is correct -- hover to `--color-primary` since it's a constructive action (moving something forward), not destructive.\n\nNo blocking issues. No new design tokens needed. This should be the fastest visual implementation yet -- it's essentially a stripped-down version of the Waiting For page without the person field.\n\nReady for implementation."
  }
